summary: 01/02/2016: At least 12 armed assailants seized the Malheur National Wildlife Refuge headquarters in Princeton, Oregon, United States. summary: 01/11/2016: An assailant armed with a machete attacked and injured a Jewish schoolteacher in Marseille, Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur region, France. An unidentified individual claimed responsibility for the incident and stated that he believed France did not respect Islam and protected Jewish civilians. He also asserted that he carried out the attack on behalf of the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL).
motive: An unidentified individual claimed responsibility for the incident and stated that he believed France did not respect Islam and protected Jewish civilians. He also asserted that he carried out the attack on behalf of the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL).

scite3: "French Jews Advised To Hide Their Identities After Anti-Semitic Attacks," Opposing Views, January 13, 2016.

summary: 01/11/2016: Security forces identified and arrested two suicide bombers in Jalalabad city, Nangarhar province, Afghanistan. No group claimed responsibility for the incident; however, sources attributed the attempted attack to the Taliban.

location: The incident occurred in the Baghdad al-Jadeeda area in the 9 Nissan neighborhood.
summary: 01/11/2016: An explosives-laden vehicle detonated at Al-Jawhara shopping center in Baghdad al-Jadeeda neighborhood, Baghdad city, Baghdad governorate, Iraq. Following the blast, additional assailants, including a suicide bomber, entered the shopping center. At least 12 people were taken hostage inside the building. Three of the hostages were killed while the other nine victims were released. Overall, at least 21 people, including three assailants, were killed and 50 others were injured in the attack; the victims included civilians and security forces members. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) claimed responsibility for the incident.
gname: Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL)
weapdetail: An explosives-laden vehicle, explosives-laden vests, and automatic firearms were used in the attack.
propcomment: A mall was damaged in this attack.
addnotes: Casualty numbers for this incident conflict across sources. Following GTD protocol, the lowest reliable estimates are reported here.

scite2: "Gunmen storm Baghdad mall, kill at least 18, Daesh takes responsibility," Mumbai Mirror, January 12, 2016.
scite3: "Gunmen enter Baghdad mall after explosion that kills 7 - sources," Reuters UK, January 11, 2016.

summary: 01/11/2016: A suicide bomber detonated at a casino in Muqdadiyah, Diyala governorate, Iraq. This was one of two coordinated attacks in Muqdadiyah; this first bombing was designed to draw a crowd. In addition to the bomber, at least 20 people were killed and 50 others were injured across both blasts. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) claimed responsibility for the incidents.

summary: 01/11/2016: Assailants fired projectiles that landed and detonated in Barwana, Al Anbar governorate, Iraq. At least 12 assailants were killed and five soldiers were injured in the ensuing clash. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) claimed responsibility for the attack.

location: The incident occurred in the Muqdadiyah district.
summary: 01/11/2016: An explosive device detonated at a civilian residence in Al-Asiri, Muqdadiyah district, Diyala governorate, Iraq. There were no reported casualties in the blast. This was one of seven bombings at houses in Al-Asiri and one of 51 attacks in and around Muqdadiyah overnight. No group claimed responsibility; however, sources attributed the incidents to Asa'ib Ahl al-Haqq and the Badr Brigades.
motive: The specific motive is unknown; however, sources suspected that the attack, which targeted members of the Sunni community, may have been part of a larger trend of sectarian violence between Iraq's minority Sunni and majority Shiite communities.
propcomment: A house was damaged in this attack.
scite1: "Reprisals reported in Iraq after bombs," BBC, January 12, 2016.
scite2: "IS ignites sectarian tensions in multiple Iraq bombings," Middle East Eye, January 12, 2016.

location: The incident occurred in the Masheeq area.
summary: 01/28/2016: A suicide bomber detonated an explosives-laden vehicle at a checkpoint outside of the presidential palace in Masheeq area, Aden city, Adan governorate, Yemen. In addition to the bomber, seven people were killed and 12 others were injured in the blast. The Adan-Abyan Province of the Islamic State claimed responsibility for the incident.
gname: Adan-Abyan Province of the Islamic State
propcomment: It is unknown if any property was damaged in this attack.
addnotes: Casualty numbers for this incident conflict across sources. Following GTD protocol, the lowest reliable estimates are reported here.
scite1: "Yemen blast kills seven near presidential palace," Al Jazeera, January 28, 2016.
scite2: "Car bombing near Yemen's presidential palace, 9 soldiers killed," Xinhua News Agency, January 28, 2016.
scite3: "Daesh claims attack on Hadi's palace," The Gulf Today, January 28, 2016.

summary: 01/28/2016: Assailants fired artillery at Al Thawrah Hospital in Taizz governorate, Yemen. At least 24 civilians were injured in the attack. No group claimed responsibility for the incident; however, sources attributed the attack to Huthis.
weapdetail: Artillery was used in the attack.
propcomment: A hospital was damaged in this attack.
scite1: "Yemen: Security Roundup 2000 GMT 28 January 2016," OSC Summary, January 28, 2016.

location: The incident occurred in the Usayfirah neighborhood.
summary: 01/28/2016: Assailants opened fire on Abd-al-Aziz al-Sab'i in Usayfirah neighborhood, Taizz city, Taizz governorate, Yemen. Al-Sab'i, a Popular Resistance Committees (Yemen) commander, was killed in the attack. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
scite1: "Yemen: Security Roundup 2000 GMT 28 January 2016," OSC Summary, January 28, 2016.

summary: 01/28/2016: An explosive device detonated in a pharmacy in Khost city, Khost province, Afghanistan. One person was killed and five others were injured in the attack. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
propcomment: A pharmacy was damaged in this attack.
scite1: "Afghanistan: Explosion in Khost Store Lab Kills One, Injures Five People," Pajhwok Afghan News, January 28, 2016.
scite2: "Highlights: Pakistan Pashto Press January 29, 2016," OSC Summary, January 29, 2016.

location: The incident occurred in the Jamil Chowk area.
summary: 01/28/2016: Multiple explosive devices planted near an electricity tower were discovered and defused along Ring Road near Jamil Chowk, Peshawar, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, Pakistan. No group claimed responsibility for the attack.
weapdetail: A homemade explosive device consisting of a canister containing 20 kilograms of explosives was used in the attack.
scite1: "Major terror bid foiled, five bombs defused in Peshawar," Daily Regional Times, January 29, 2016.
scite2: "Pakistan: Peshawar on edge as police foil terror plot," Dawn Online, January 28, 2016.
scite3: "Highlights: Pakistan Pashto Press January 29, 2016," OSC Summary, January 29, 2016.
